```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def solution():
    labels = ['Flooded', 'Non-Flooded']
    data = [1, 5]
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.pie(data, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('Flooded vs Non-Flooded Houses')
    return fig
```

```python
import math

def solution():
    counts = [570, 663, 590, 737, 639, 534]
    gsd = 0.125241336251  # metres per pixel
    min_px = min(counts)
    area_m2 = min_px * gsd**2
    extra_px = math.ceil((15 - area_m2) / (gsd**2))
    return str((min_px, round(area_m2, 6), extra_px))
```
